About a year has passed since I first "woke up".[r]
I have never once thought that my experiences in that world were a dream, not even for a second.[r]
The quantity and quality of memories, and the vividness of those experiences, are just too different from a typical dream.[l][r]
Without a doubt, that layered city was a world I experienced firsthand.[r]
I was born there, raised there, lived, fell, wandered, and died.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
But at the same time, I also have my life and past memories in modern-day Japan.[l][r]
I was born in some rural town, had a mundane childhood, and for some reason pursued a degree in aerospace and mechanical engineering, earning a degree and joining my current company.[r]
These memories also feel real, and my parents and grandparents are alive and well back home.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
So, I'll ask myself this question.[r]
Which set of memories is more real?[l][r]
The answer is, "Both are real." It might sound contradictory, but it is.[r]
As I kept questioning myself like this, I figured it didn't matter anymore.[r]
There are, after all, unsolvable problems like the Last Thursdayism hypothesis.[l][r]
Even though I might have come to terms with it, certain doubts or sentimental feelings just wouldn't leave me.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
I wonder what's become of that city and those girls now.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[bg  time="1500"  method="crossfade"  storage="office.jpg"  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
A subcontractor for a certain aircraft manufacturer. This particular office in this world is my workplace.[r]
Right now, I'm struggling with a new design team for parts.[l][r]
But it's a shame. Many designs I saw in that world surpass the current technology here.[l][r]
I genuinely feel it's a pity. Back then, I only cared about practical flight and didn't bother understanding those seemingly theoretical and unusable designs.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
If I could have understood even one of those futuristic technologies (as I believe they were) and manifested it in this world, I could have easily made a fortune.[l][r]
Well, anyway, it's impossible now. I heave a sigh. The backrest I leaned against made a creaking noise.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"Ishii, did you see the email from admin?"[r]
A colleague asks me from the side.[l][r]
"Which email?"[r]
"The one about that weird inquiry from a student. Apparently, they've sent the same email to our competitors and partner companies too.[l][r]
From what I skimmed, it might be related to you, Ishii."[r]
...What the heck? Why would I have anything to do with some spam-like inquiry?[r]
I don't say it aloud but feel really annoyed as I open the company mail app. Is this it?[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

