"Chito...? Hey Chito, are you okay?!"[l][r]
"Ugh... uh... uh..." The sound of irregular breathing and a different kind of sobbing continued.[l][r]
...This is bad. Chito might be having a panic attack.[l][r]

[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
But without knowing where she is, there's nothing I can do except talk to her through this phone.[l][r]
Damn... Asking about Yuri at this moment was too careless...![l][r]
What should I do? Tell her to hang up and call for an ambulance? Or ask if there's someone nearby to help her?[l][r]
Either way, if Chito faints or goes into a frenzy, there’s nothing I can do.[r]
What should I do?... What can I do?! Just then...[l][r]
[cm]"Gasp... Haa... Haa... I'm okay... I just got a little surprised..."[r]
Chito's weak voice vibrated in my eardrum.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"Are you alright?" I ask.[r]
"Yes... I'm okay... now..."[l][r]
The irregular breathing and the hoarse voice. It didn’t sound okay at all.[r]
I forgot that Chito was probably at school and that I was at work, and just hoped for her to calm down.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
Eventually, her breathing became more regular, and her voice regained a bit of strength.[l][r]
"Yes... I'm... okay now. Sorry, Ishii, I can't talk about the details yet..."[l][r]
"Oh... okay. No worries. I'm sorry for confusing you... for making things worse."[r]
That’s right. There’s no way we can discuss all our experiences in that harsh world over the phone.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

